title: Starmer says any attack on his cabinet is ‘completely unacceptable’ and adds Streeting is doing a great job – UK politics live
summary: Kemi Badenoch has questioned Keir Starmer regarding a "toxic culture" at Downing Street, alleging misconduct within the government. In response, Prime Minister Rishi Sunak has denied any involvement in authorizing briefings against potential rival candidates. The exchange highlights ongoing tensions and concerns about political integrity within the government.

title: ONS plans to scrap reports on health and crime to improve quality of data
summary: The UK's statistics agency has unveiled a 'recovery' plan in response to growing concerns regarding the reliability of its data. This initiative aims to address and rectify issues related to the accuracy and integrity of statistical information. The move comes as part of efforts to restore public confidence in the agency's outputs.
